{{flavour|A ring that brings its wearer more in contact with the powers of fire. It grants resistance to heat and enhances fire magic, but causes vulnerability to cold.}}

A [[ring of fire]] is a [[ring]] that enhances the [[spell power|power]] of [[fire magic]] spells. Additionally, it provides one level of [[fire resistance]] (rF+) and one negative level of [[cold resistance]] (rC-).

==Tips & Tricks==
*A ring of fire can serve as a poor man's [[ring of protection from fire]] in a pinch, particularly if you should encounter a [[Volcano]] mini branch.
*You don't want to be vulnerable to any element for too long, since you (the player) can always forget about it. Even if you use [[Fire Magic]], you'll want a source of [[cold resistance]] to counteract the vulnerability. 
:If you don't have a way to negate rC-, Fire specialists can still find this ring useful - just remember to remove it against icy enemies.

==History==
*Prior to [[0.19]], rings of fire provided a negative [[Ice Magic]] enhancer.

